            , who lives in Drury-lane. On the 2d of April, in the evening, I left these brooms outside the <placeName id="t18240407-131-crimeloc734">Alphabet public-house in Stanhope-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240407-131-crimeloc734" type="placeName" value="Alphabet public-house in Stanhope-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240407-131-crimeloc734" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-131-off732 t18240407-131-crimeloc734"></join>; a boy came in and gave an alarm - I went to the door, and they were gone. I had not left them above a minute.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240407-131-person1229">
                  CHARLES 
                  PENDRILL
               <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1229" type="surname" value="PENDRILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1229" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the public-house. I followed Norris out, ran down Duke-street into Drury-lane, and collared the prisoner with the brooms; he immediately threw them off his shoulder, and used abusive language to me. I secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240407-131-person1230">
                  THOMAS 
                  GRAY
               <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1230" type="surname" value="GRAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1230" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-131-person1230" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am twelve years old. I saw three men sitting at a door about seven houses from the Alphabet; two told the other one to go and get them; the two ran off to a cook-shop - the other went and got the brooms. I know two of them, but cannot say whether the prisoner was the third or not, he was not the one who took them; the two remained at the cook-shop till<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182404070057"></xptr>they saw the other had got them, and then all set off. I went in and told the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man stood at the corner of a court with them, and asked me to carry them to Newport-market.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18240407-131-verdict735" type="verdictDescription">
